Prague MHD takes us on Wednesday for the first time with the chip
On Wednesday, October 1, 2008, it is written in the history of the Prague Transport Company the date when the first passengers enter the subway, tram and bus with an electronic bonus in their pockets instead of a paper ticket.
This can now be purchased by almost one hundred thousand people who own the Opencard chip card.
Passengers can purchase the 30-day, 90-day and annual bonus (this will be valid from 1 January 2009) and simultaneously load it on their chip card at the info centers and posts of the transportation company at the stations of Metro, Muzeum, Můstek, Nádraží Holešovice, Kolýl, Andšlyl, Roztyl
Bonuses can be purchased on the internet from yesterday on the transportation company’s pages, www.dpp.cz.
The service, until the afternoon, was used by more than 400 people.
Those who begin to use the internet as a form of trading may definitely begin to forget the ticket sales positions at the subway stations, where they so far had to regularly tail to get a normal ticket out.
The bonus is purchased on the internet, and the Opencard card will recharge it at one of the 13 subsidiaries of the Municipal Library.
“In these places there is available to passengers a window with prepared staff that helps stakeholders with purchasing online and also with the recharge of the bonus purchased on their card,” said project spokesman Martin Opatrný.
In addition to the library, it will also be possible to recharge the electronic bonus on the Opencard on the automatic sales machines located in some lobsters of the subway.
How are these sales machines?
They are red, they remind us of a ticket picking machine and travellers probably have already been fixed on them at the stations of Roztyly, Budějovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská.
“There are now five in the city but by the end of the year it would have to be eighty,” Opatrný said.
The bonus is controlled by the machine instead of the driver
The use of the machine, which will begin to work tomorrow, is simple.
Just enter in it the Opencard chip card and the previously paid bonus will be loaded only on it.
Electronic bonds from tomorrow are valid not only in the capital but also in its surroundings.
That is, in circumvalation trains and bus lines from the numbers 300 to 499 that mainly use the inhabitants of the localities of Central Bohemia.
“In the trains enrolled on integrated transport from Prague there are reviewers equipped with a reader card that will help confirm the validity of the time and the bonus zone,” Filip Drapal of the Ropid organization sets the timetables for collective transport from Prague.
Circular buses have their reading cards mounted on the driver’s box.
When you enter, you need not only to show the card to the driver but also to accompany it with the Opencard at the place intended for this on the side of the Box.
As a result, the driver controls the validity of the bonus.
“If the passenger needs to verify the validity of the obligations there is nothing easier than asking the driver for this information,” Dr. Drapal said.
Passengers who do not travel in surrounding buses and do not remember when the validity of the bonus is finished may be directed to the sales machines where the cards are recharged.
Here, on the machine screen, you will be shown information about the validity of your document.
